definitions.definition: An edible pulse ( Cicer arietinum ), of the family Leguminosae or Fabaceae and subfamilies Faboideae or Papilionoideae , with white or purple-blue flowers and small feathery leaves on both sides of the stem and pods containing two to three peas.
A seed of this plant; the chickpea .
